"Category: An issue proposing an enhancement or a PR with one."}, {"id": 211668062, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMTE2NjgwNjI=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/T-libs-api", "name": "T-libs-api", "color": "bfd4f2", "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the library API team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2017-03-28T14:30:14Z", "updated_at": "2017-07-26T18:03:20Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "pthreads provides [pthread_barrier_t](http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/functions/pthread_barrier_init.html).  Windows provides [synchronization barriers](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/hh706897(v=vs.85).aspx), albeit only on Windows 8 and above.\r\n\r\nUsing platform-native barriers may be smaller (e.g. on Linux/glibc, a barrier is ~third of the size of a mutex+condvar), require fewer allocations (only one `Box` for the underlying barrier, rather than separate boxes for an underlying `sys::Mutex` and `sys::Condvar`), and may take advantage of system-specific optimizations that would render them faster.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/40875/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/40875/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}